<seg id="71">The supply of goods in the SR pursuant to the provisions of Section 8 of Act No. 222/2004 Z. z. is considered to be the supply of tangible property, in which there is a change of ownership.</seg>
<seg id="72">The supply of goods shall also be deemed to be the transfer of goods owned by a taxable person from the country to another Member State, provided that such goods are dispatched or transported by that person or on his behalf to another Member State for the purposes of his business.</seg>
<seg id="73">According to the provisions of Section 43 of Law No 222/2004 Z. z. the supply of goods from the country to another Member State is exempt from VAT if the purchaser is a person identified for VAT in another Member State.</seg>
<seg id="74">The acquisition of goods from another EU Member State in the Czech Republic pursuant to Section 16 of Act No. 235/2004 Coll. means the acquisition of the right to dispose as owner of goods that is dispatched or transported by a person registered for VAT in another EU Member State.</seg>
