<seg id="76">The acquisition of goods in the czech republic from another EU Member State in the Czech Republic pursuant to Section 11 of Act No. 222/2004 Z. z. means the acquisition of the right to dispose as owner of movable tangible property sent or transported by the pros andators to the supplier or the prom or on their behalf to the country from another Member State.</seg>
<seg id="77">The tax liability in the Czech Republic is incurred by the payer when the goods are acquired in the czech republic from another Member State pursuant to the provisions of Section 20 of Act No. 222/2004 Z.z.</seg>
<seg id="78">The payer may deduct VAT under the provisions of Section 49 of Act No. 222/2004 Z. z. if the tax is applied by him on the acquisition of goods in the country from another Member State pursuant to § §11 and 11a of this Act.</seg>
<seg id="79">Triangular trade means, in accordance with the provisions of Section 17 of Act No. 235/2004 Coll., or Section 45 of Act No. 222/2004 Z. z. trade concluded between three persons registered for VAT in three different EU Member States, where the subject of the trade is the supply of the same goods between the three persons.</seg>
