<seg id="82">VIES system</seg>
<seg id="83">A VAT information exchange system has been established within the EU to control the application of the vat exemption entitlement to intra-Community supplies of goods.</seg>
<seg id="84">It includes the VIES electronic system, which allows tax authorities of EU Member States to check whether the supplier was entitled to exempt taxable transactions from VAT and, conversely, whether the acquirer has properly admitted and taxed the acquired goods.</seg>
<seg id="85">The VIES information system is not centralised within the EU.</seg>
<seg id="86">Each Member State develops its own VIES system.</seg>
<seg id="87">National systems work on a common principle and are interconnected through the EU's common communication network, the so-called 'common communication network'. CCN (Common Communication Network; see diagram below).</seg>
<seg id="88">In the Czech Republic, the VIES system was connected with an automated tax information system (hereinafter referred to as "ADIS"), in the Czech Republic with the application software of the tax information system (hereinafter referred to as "APV DIS").</seg>
<seg id="89">These systems are used by the tax authorities as technical support for executive and management activities in the management of taxes and fees.</seg>
<seg id="90">International administrative cooperation</seg>
<seg id="91">Through international administrative cooperation, the tax administration of each EU member country obtains information on tax entities that, without such cooperation, would not have been able to obtain on its own.</seg>
<seg id="92">The main objective of international administrative cooperation is to combat tax evasion and tax losses.</seg>
<seg id="93">According to Council Regulation (EC) No 1798/2003, each Member State shall establish, within the internal organisational structure, a central unit in the field of administrative cooperation between EU Member States in the management of VAT, the so-called 'VAT'. CLO (Central Liaison Office).</seg>
<seg id="94">In the Czech Republic, the Ministry of Finance – Central Financial and Tax Directorate, where the International Cooperation in VAT Management Unit (hereinafter referred to as the "MF CLO") was established, performs the tasks resulting from international cooperation.</seg>
<seg id="95">The function of CLO in the SR is performed by the Tax Directorate of the Czech Technical Authority, the Department of International Administrative Cooperation (hereinafter referred to as "DR CLO").</seg>
<seg id="96">These departments, inter alia, communicate with EU foreign administrations, in particular in the field of information exchange within the VIES system, exchange of spontaneous information and information at the request of EU tax administrations, coordination of multilateral (simultaneous) tax controls, verification of tax identification numbers (hereinafter referred to as "VAT registration numbers") of persons registered for VAT in other EU Member States and communicate with the European Commission.</seg>
<seg id="97">In order to investigate an intra-Community transaction or to obtain further information relating to a particular tax entity, the tax authorities send requests for information to the EU via MF CLO or DR CLO.</seg>
<seg id="98">Through these requests, they obtain information from the requested Member States which they can use for the correct determination of VAT.</seg>
<seg id="99">Requests for information are mostly sent between CLO of EU Member States in electronic form, using a standardised SCAC form.</seg>
