<seg id="352">5.2 International Exchange of L3 Level Information</seg>
<seg id="353">The exchange of information at L3 level is initiated by local tax authorities who send their requests for information (hereinafter referred to as "ŽOI") or spontaneous information (hereinafter referred to as "SPI"), relating to a particular tax entity or transaction, via the MF CLO, respectively.</seg>
<seg id="354">dr clo to another EU country. The aim of the ZOI is, for example, to ensure that the proof of the execution of the transaction in the context of intra-Community transactions, examination of a particular VAT number, etc.</seg>
<seg id="355">In the case of SPI, it is a communication of information relevant to tax authorities in another EU member state.</seg>
<seg id="356">Cooperation in the field of information exchange is regulated by Council Regulation (EC) No 1798/2003.</seg>
