<seg id="99">By registering the tax warehouse, tax warehouse operator or authorized recipient in the SysNed application software, this information is automatically transferred to the "System for Exchange of Excise Data" database (hereinafter referred to as "SEED").</seg>
<seg id="100">3. Preparation and cooperation</seg>
<seg id="101">The first coordination meeting between representatives of the SAO-CR and representatives of the SAO SR, at which a specific procedure for cooperation in the implementation of parallel controls in the field of excise duties was discussed, took place in January 2006.</seg>
<seg id="102">The two sides became familiar with excise legislation and the organisation of excise tax management in both states.</seg>
<seg id="103">Particular attention was paid to the procedure of the customs authorities of the Czech Republic and the Czech Republic in the authorisation or in the initiation and cessation of transport of products subject to excise duty under the conditional exemption procedure and the exchange of information between the excise tax authorities of both countries.</seg>
<seg id="104">At the meeting it was agreed that the Czech and Slovak parties: - will process the total data on the quantity of excise goods transported from the Czech Republic to slovakia and vice versa, whose transport was started during the controlled period - compare data on transports of mineral oils - combined nomenclature code 2710 and 2711 and alcohol - combined nomenclature code 2207 and 2208 under the conditional exemption scheme initiated in the Czech Republic and terminated in the Slovak Republic and vice versa in the months of November 2004 and September 2005.</seg>
