<seg id="106">Tables 1 and No 2 show the total quantity of products subject to excise duty which have been transported under the conditional exemption scheme between Czech and Slovak tax entities during the period audited.</seg>
<seg id="107">4. Comparison of records of the transport of goods under the suspensive exemption procedure</seg>
<seg id="108">The SAO-CR handed over to the Slovak side a database of transports completed in the Czech Republic, which contained a total of 5,876 items listed on the accompanying documents, of which 5,738 items related to mineral oils, 134 items of alcohol and 4 items of tobacco products.</seg>
<seg id="109">The SAO SR forwarded to the Czech side a database of transports completed in the Slovak Republic containing a total of 3,319 items on the accompanying documents, of which 696 were covered mineral oil, 2 066 items of alcohol and 557 items of tobacco products.</seg>
<seg id="110">The SAO-ČR compared the data on the transports mentioned in the records of the commenced transports in the Czech Republic with the data on completed transports registered in the Slovak Republic.</seg>
