<seg id="187">ELO ČR sent ELO SR 25 requests to the MVS.</seg>
<seg id="188">The customs authorities in the Czech Republic most often checked the data given in the accompanying documents, in particular the quantity of products received or dispatched or whether the consignor of the products specified in the accompanying document is entitled to dispose of products subject to excise duty, if this fact could not be verified in the international SEED database.</seg>
<seg id="189">The received REQUESTS for THE EMV were forwarded in both countries to the customs authorities locally responsible for the consignor or consignor of excise products.</seg>
<seg id="190">The customs authorities checked the requested data and notified the result of the investigation through ELO to the other Member State.</seg>
<seg id="191">6. Summary</seg>
<seg id="192">The cooperation of the SAO-CR and the SAO SR made it possible to compare the basic legislation governing excise duties in both states, the procedure of the customs authorities of the Czech Republic and the Czech Republic in the initiation and termination of the transport of products under the conditional exemption procedure between the two states, the registration of such transports and the comparison of information between customs authorities in the framework of international cooperation.</seg>
<seg id="193">6.1 By comparing the legislation governing excise duties in the Czech Republic and the Czech Republic, differences were found:</seg>
<seg id="194">(a) in the procedure of tax entities and tax authorities when initiating the transport of products under the suspensive exemption scheme.</seg>
<seg id="195">The transport of products under the conditional exemption regime can be started by a tax entity in the Czech Republic only with the agreement of the tax administrator, who will allow the start of transport, provided that the transported products have been provided with a tax security amount of the tax attributable to them.</seg>
<seg id="196">The commencement of the transport of products under the suspensive exemption scheme in the SR shall not be subject to the authorisation of the tax authorities.</seg>
<seg id="197">During the period audited, the tax entity was obliged to notify the tax authorities of the start of the transport of alcohol and tobacco products.</seg>
<seg id="198">The transport of mineral oils, beer and wine could have started without informing the tax administrator of this fact.</seg>
<seg id="199">In 2006, amendments to all excise laws were progressively adopted in the Czech Republic, according to which the consignor of goods under the conditional exemption procedure is obliged to send a copy of copy No 1 of the accompanying document electronically or by fax to the customs office which is locally competent to the consignor before the start of transport;</seg>
<seg id="200">(b) within the time limits for dispatch of copy No 3 of the accompanying document.</seg>
<seg id="201">The recipient in the Czech Republic is obliged to send copy No. 3 and 4 of the accompanying document to the tax administrator for verification no later than the next working day after the end of the transport.</seg>
<seg id="202">Certified copy No. 3 is obliged to send to the consignor no later than the next working day after its receipt from the tax administrator.</seg>
<seg id="203">The consignee in the SR is obliged to send to the consignor of the products copy No. 3 certified by the tax administrator and the recipient of the products no later than 15. the day of the month following the month in which he received the goods.</seg>
<seg id="204">6.2. The customs authorities in the Czech Republic keep electronic records of the transport of products under the suspensive exemption procedure.</seg>
<seg id="205">The content and method of keeping this register is not regulated by law in the Czech Republic or in the Czech Republic.</seg>
<seg id="206">The customs authorities in both countries shall enter in the register all the data from the accompanying documents on the basis of which the transport is carried out.</seg>
<seg id="207">There is currently no single electronic system for monitoring the transport of goods under the conditional exemption procedure between Member States of the European Union to allow excise managers in each Member State to obtain real-time information on the transport of goods.</seg>
<seg id="208">Pursuant to Decision 1152/2003/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 16 December 2003 on the protection of the european communities's products,[ The information shall be asked to be asked by the Authorities of the It is envisaged that the electronic system for monitoring the movement of products subject to excise duty should be established.</seg>
<seg id="209">On the basis of the contract for cooperation in control activities, the Czech party handed over to the Slovak side a database of transport of products under the conditional exemption procedure initiated in slovakia and completed in the Czech Republic.</seg>
<seg id="210">The database contained 5 876 items relating to transported mineral oils, alcohol and tobacco products.</seg>
<seg id="211">The Slovak party handed over to the Czech party a database of transport of products under the conditional exemption procedure initiated in the Czech Republic and terminated in slovakia.</seg>
<seg id="212">The database contained 3 319 items relating to transported mineral oils, alcohol and tobacco products.</seg>
<seg id="213">The Czech side compared the data on the transports mentioned in the records of commenced transports in the Czech Republic with the registration of transports completed in the Slovak Republic.</seg>
<seg id="214">The Slovak side compared data on the transport of goods under the conditional exemption procedure initiated in Slovakia and terminated in the Czech Republic.</seg>
<seg id="215">The comparison of data was hampered by the fact that the quantity of goods transported was not uniformly reported in the databases.</seg>
<seg id="216">In cases where it was not possible to clearly assign data on individual transports in both records, an inspection of the accompanying documents was carried out and breaches of the suspensive exemption regime and cases of tax evasion were not detected.</seg>
<seg id="217">On the basis of the findings of parallel controls, it can be concluded that Member States can obtain valuable information from the transport records to improve the management of excise duties.</seg>
<seg id="218">The establishment of an electronic system for the transport and control of excise goods within the meaning of Decision No 1152/2003/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council will allow for the electronic transmission of the accompanying document and more effective control of movements under the conditional exemption procedure within the territory of the European Union.</seg>
