<seg id="617">5. Conclusion</seg>
<seg id="618">The cooperation of the two SAIs on parallel controls of VAT management met the objectives set by the SAO and BRH.</seg>
<seg id="619">The two SAIs have better understood each other's systems in the following areas: • intra-community transactions, • VAT risk management, in particular as regards the selection of risk-prone transactions, • assistance in the recovery of VAT receivables and • VAT control for large tax entities.</seg>
<seg id="620">Thanks to mutual cooperation, differences in strategies for detecting VAT fraud cases as well as differences in the above areas of VAT management in the Czech Republic and Germany have been revealed.</seg>
<seg id="621">The control findings were compared and best practices were identified on the basis of them.</seg>
<seg id="622">In addition, the two SAIs hope that the results achieved will provide an impetus for stakeholders to start a debate on approaches and strategies within Member States, including at European Commission level.</seg>
<seg id="623">The extremely valuable experience and knowledge gained from the cooperation of the two SAIs can serve as an encouragement for the implementation of future control actions in the field of VAT management.</seg>
